Billboard calls &ldquo;Miley Cyrus and her Dead Petz&rdquo; as the 'catalyst' of pop stars going against the traditional pop rollout of albums, like Lana Del Rey &amp; Ariana Grande today. <br />
<br />
&ldquo;A predecessor of today&rsquo;s rule-breaking, tradion-flipping pop scene...ahead of its time.&rdquo;

Harry Styles opens up about his white privilege &amp; how he tries to make everyone feel included. <br />
<br />
&ldquo;I&rsquo;m aware that as a white male, I don&rsquo;t go through the same things as a lot of the people that come to my shows. I cant claim that I know what it&rsquo;s like, because I don&rsquo;t.&rdquo;

Normani reveals that she studied Britney Spears&rsquo;s 2001 VMAs&nbsp;performance to prepare for hers! <br />
<br />
&ldquo;I study...I watch Britney&rsquo;s performances with the snake - the most iconic moment. I feel like the VMAs is where the biggest moments in pop culture happen!&rdquo;

Lizzo says Rihanna praised her VMAs&nbsp;performance:<br />
<br />
&quot;Rihanna DM'ed me to tell me that I performed good. She said I f**ked the stage like it was my side b***h. Don't get mad, Rihanna. I am not trying to blow up your spot, but that was a hard a** line! I might take that line.&quot;

